          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Paradox Trail #502 begins at the end of Forest Service Road #660, Pinto Mesa Road, and ends at the National Forest Boundary. The trail starts west, then northwest and descend off Pinto Mesa. After about 0.4, it turn southeast and at about 1 miles it veer to the southwest as it wanders its way toward Coal Canyon. It ends at the National Forest Boundary which is also the edge of the <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/gmug/specialplaces/?cid=stelprdb5245708\" rel=\"nofollow\">Tabeguache Area</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd541383.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Ref Trail Map</a>   <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/gmug/maps-pubs/?cid=stelprdb5441230\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Reference Instructions</a></p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p><strong>From Nucla:</strong> On Hwy 97, turn east on East 4th Ave. and travel approximately 0.5 miles. Turn north on 25 Mesa/Delta-Nucla Road, which becomes Forest Service Road #503 at the National Forest boundary, and continue for approximately 7 miles to FSR #660, Pinto Mesa Road. Turn north onto FSR #660 and continue for approximately 2.5 miles to the beginning of the trail at the end of the road.</p><p><strong>From Delta:</strong> Turn west on Highway 348, 6th Street. Travel west and south on HWY 348 for approximately 4 miles to 25 Mesa Road. Continue on 25 Mesa Road for approximately 18 miles the National Forest Boundary where 25 Mesa Road becomes Forest Service Road #503. Continue on FSR #503 for approximately 9.3 miles to FSR #402, Divide Road. Turn south on FSR #402 and continue for approximately 0.9 miles to FSR #503 South, Delta-Nulca Road. Continue south on FSR #503 for approximately 14.5 miles to FSR #660, Pinto Mesa Road. Follow FSR #660 for approximately 2.5 miles to the end of the road where the trail begins.</p>",
