          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Big Fish Trail begins at the Big Fish Trailhead in the <a href=\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/whiteriver/recarea/?recid=40783\" rel=\"nofollow\">Himes Peak Campground</a>. The trail crosses the White River on a narrow foot bridge, then enters the <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/whiteriver/recarea/?recid=81112\" rel=\"nofollow\">Flat Tops Wilderness</a> where regulations apply. The trail follows Big Fish Creek .75 miles to Bessie's Falls, then continues another mile to Big Fish Lake. One-half mile beyond Big Fish Lake, the trail starts a twisting, two-mile climb onto the Flat Tops, where it joins <a href=\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/whiteriver/recarea/?recid=40807\" rel=\"nofollow\">Oyster Lake Trail #1825</a>.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5186545.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Print a trail description and map</a> (.pdf)</p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p>The Big Fish Trail begins 46 miles east of Meeker at the Himes Peak Campground.</p><p>From Meeker, CO take Colorado Highway 13 east for 1 mile, then turn right (east) on Rio Blanco County Road 8 and follow this for 39 miles. Turn south on Trappers Lake Road #205, and continue 6 miles to the Himes Peak Campground. The Big Fish Trailhead is on the left as you enter the campground.</p>",
