          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Located near the Summit Rest Area/Visitors Center/Lincoln Monument. Access to the Tie City and Happy Jack trail systems via the Headquarters and Crow Creek Loop Trails. Open seasonally weather permitting but you can park at the gate and hike in in the winter. Trails are very wet and muddy in the springtime. One vault toilet some picnic table available. No potable water. </p><p>Located in the Pole Mountain area and managed by the Laramie Ranger District. </p>",
