          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Byers Peak Trailhead provides access to the <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/arp/recarea/?recid=80800\" rel=\"nofollow\">Byers Peak Wilderness</a>.</p><p>This is an unconventional trailhead in that hikers must travel over 1.8 miles of road before arriving at the trail to the peak. Visitors are welcome to bicycle this first 1.8 miles and leave the bicycle at the provided bike rack.</p><p><strong>Note:</strong> The access road to this trailhead is closed to motor vehicles between Nov. 15 and June 15.</p><p>View a COTREX area map <a href=\"https://trails.colorado.gov/trailheads/byers-peak-904\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>",
