          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Deer Lake Trail connects <a href=\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/whiteriver/recarea/?recid=41229&actid=104\" rel=\"nofollow\">Island Lakes Trail #1842</a> to <a href=\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/whiteriver/recarea/?recid=40767\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chinese Wall Trail #1803</a>. From Island Lakes Trail, Deer Lake Trail branches north and follows a bench that overlooks the Island Lake and Derby Creek drainages. After 2 miles, the trail becomes steep and narrow as it drops to down to Deer Lake; this section can be hazardous to pack strings. From Deer Lake, the trail climbs 1 mile to the Flat Tops plateau where it joins the Chinese Wall Trail.</p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p>Access to the Deer Lake Trail is located 50 miles east of Meeker, CO.</p><p>From Meeker, CO take Colorado Highway 13 east for 1 mile, then turn right (east) on Rio Blanco County Road 8 and follow this for 39 miles. Turn south on Trappers Lake Road #205, and travel 10 miles to the Outlet Trailhead.</p><p>Follow the Arthur E. Carhart Trail #1815 around the east side of Trappers Lake to Trappers Lake Trail # 1816. Take Trappers Lake Trail #1816 for 4 miles to the head of Fraser Creek, where Island Lakes Trail #1842 begins. Follow Island Lakes Trail 2.5 miles to Deer Lake Trail #1802.</p>",
