          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Cameron Pass is located around 65 miles west of Fort Collins on Highway 14. The area offers abundant winter recreation opportunities, including snowshoeing, cross-country skiing, scenic driving, wildlife viewing, snowmobiling, and ice fishing. Snowmobiling is not allowed in wilderness areas. The <a href=\"http://www.parks.state.co.us/parks/stateforest/Pages/StateForestStateParkHome.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">State Forest State Park</a>, which is west of Cameron Pass, also has abundant recreation activities.     </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5446931.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cameron Pass trails, page 1 (pdf, 282 KB)</a></p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5446932.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cameron Pass trails, page 2 (pdf, 116 KB)</a>      </p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5446937.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Winter Recreation map (pdf, 6.66 MB)</a>                                             </p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/arp/workingtogether/volunteering/?cid=stelprdb5213201\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cameron Pass Nordic Ranger Program </a></p>",
