          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Little Dolores Trail #648 is a two track which forks to the right off of the Fruita Division Rd #400 and heads north to an open parking area. It eventually reaches a fenceline that separates the forest from private land.  The trail continues  for another .38 miles through the fenceline and ends at a stock pond on private land. </p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd542987.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Ref Trail Map</a>   <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/gmug/maps-pubs/?cid=stelprdb5441230\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Reference Instructions</a></p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p><strong>UPPER ACCESS</strong>:</p><p>From the Glade Park Store travel 9.2 miles to the Forest Boundary on Fruita Division Rd #400.  From the Forest Boundary travel past the Mud Springs and Haypress campgrounds 2.8 miles to the Little Dolores Trailhead. </p><p><strong>LOWER ACCESS:</strong></p><p>Little Dolores Trail ends at the Forest/Private Boundary; there is no access from the lower end.</p>",
