          "FacilityDescription": "<ul><li><strong>“Campers staying at Big Meadows between September 7 and 11, 2018 can expect loud noises between 9 am and 6 pm due to a blasting project in the Spruce Lakes area, approximately 5 miles southwest of the campground”.</strong></li></ul><p>This trailhead is located at the reservoir boatramp on the northeast corner of the lake.</p><p>The facility consists of a parking lot, pit toilet, and trail signing.  This is a major trailhead to the Weminuche Wilderness and Archuleta Lake as well as a connector to the Continental Divide National Scenic Trail (CDNST).</p>",
