          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Bucktail Creek Spur Trail #659.1A begins at Forest Service Road #503 and ends at an intersection with the Bucktail Creek Trail #659. This short trail provides access to FSR #503 from the Bucktail Creek Trail which comes to an end at the National Forest Boundary.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd541083.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Ref Trail Map </a>  <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/gmug/maps-pubs/?cid=stelprdb5441230\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Reference Instructions</a></p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p><strong>From Montrose: </strong>Travel west on Highway 90 for approximately 23 miles to the intersection with Forest Service Road #402, Divide Road. Follow FSR #402 for approximately 16.5 miles to FSR #503. Turn south onto FSR #503, Delta-Nucla Road, and continue for approximately 13 miles to the trail access on the southeast side of the road.</p>",
