          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The County Line Trails is located in the central portion of the Grand Mesa. The western access is off Highway 65 at the County Line Winter Trailhead. The trail receives frequent grooming a moderate level of difficulty. Trail miles total 7.8 miles and offers winter trail loop options in open coniferous forest. (<a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprdb5286904.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Winter Trail Map</a>)</p>",
