          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Located 2.2 miles east of County Road 82E on the south side of Johnny Park Road (National Forest System Road 118), the trailhead is marked with a small sign near a minor saddle. This trailhead provides access to the <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/arp/recreation/hiking/recarea/?recid=28216&actid=50\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bright Extension Trail</a>.</p><p>Acccess to the trailhead is seasonal. For current information on road openings and closures, check the <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/goto/arp/roads\" rel=\"nofollow\">Road Status Table</a>.</p><p>View an area map <a href=\"http://trails.colorado.gov/trailheads/bright-extension-2170\" rel=\"nofollow\">here.</a></p>",
