          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Don't want to pitch a tent?... Try one of the many historic properties that the Forest has restored and made available to you for overnight rental.</p><p>Early 1900's homestead, an old Forest Service Gaurd Station or an 1880's mining camp. There are many opportunities to experience the bygone eras. The amenities, activities and fees vary from cabin to cabin. The most current information is available at <a href=\"http://www.recreation.gov\" rel=\"nofollow\"><u>www.recreation.gov</u></a>.</p><p>Six different cabins are currently available. One is open year-round and the others are generally available May through October, weather permitting. Check back, as we are continually working towards adding historic cabins to this program.</p><p>Just bring a bedroll, long johns and a pot of coffee to experience these unique and wonderful settings.</p>",
