          "FacilityDescription": "<p>This boating site is located on Rampart Reservoir. Swimming, wading, and all body contact with the water in the reservoir is prohibited.</p><p>All dates are weather dependent. Dates of operation below are dates visitors may expect full service. </p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p>From Colorado Springs, Colorado, travel west on Hwy 24 for about 18 miles to Woodland Park. Turn north on Baldwin (which turns into Rampart Range Road). Go about 2 miles to Loy Creek Road turn right and then to FDR 300 turn right (Rampart Range Road). Follow signs. Rampart Reservoir entrance is about 4 miles further on the left side of the road. </p>",
