          "FacilityDescription": "<h2>Overview</h2>\n<p>Please Note: Must be in possession of a horse in order to camp in the equestrian campground.</p>\n\n<p>The Indian Creek Equestrian Campground is an ideal camping site for avid horseback riders looking to explore the Indian Creek Equestrian Trail. The area provides a pleasant atmosphere plus nearby access to the Rampart Range, a well known off-highway vehicle riding area.   The area boasts wildlife like mule deer, turkey, elk and black bears. The Roxborough State Park is located to the northeast of the campground as has a reputation for its dramatic red-rock formations.</p>\n<h2>Recreation</h2>\nThe Indian Creek Trail, which is also called the Bear Creek Trail, is a loop trail that extends for 14 miles. In addition to horseback riders, mountain bikers and hikers also enjoy taking on the scenic journey. <h2>Facilities</h2>\n<p>Please Note: Must be in possession of a horse in order to camp in the equestrian campground.</p>\n\n<p>Four hitching rails and some small corrals are provided for common use. Drinking water is on hand from hydrants. There is no watering trough available. <br><br>The campground is adjacent to the Indian Creek Campground, which is available for family camping.</p>\n<h2>Natural Features</h2>\nCampsites sit among a mix of trees that provide both shade and sun throughout the day. These include Ponderosa pine, Gamble oak, Douglas fir, aspen and spruce. \n<br/><br/>\nPike-San Isabel National Forests include over a million acres of wilderness and over half of Colorado's mountain peaks that reach above 14,000 feet in altitude. ",
          "FacilityDirections": "From Sedalia, drive about 10 miles west on Highway 67 and the entrance is about a half mile from the intersection of Highway 67 and Rampart Range Rd.",
