          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Forest Trail #458 (Calf Creek Plateau Trail) is 6.6 miles long. It begins at Forest Road #788 (T44N R3W Section 35) and ends at Forest Trail #460 (T44N R3W Section 26). Part of the trail is in the Powderhorn Wilderness. Portions of the trail outside the wilderness area are open for the following uses: hiking, mountain biking, horseback riding, motorcycle trail riding, ATV trail riding. Motorized and mechanized use is prohibited in the Wilderness.</p>",
