          "FACILITYADDRESS": [],
          "FacilityAdaAccess": "",
          "FacilityDescription": "<p>Southwest of Saratoga, Wyo. on the Medicine Bow National Forest lies the Sierra Madre Range, which is a part of the main range of the Rocky Mountains.  There are two wilderness areas in the Sierra Madre Range: Huston Park Wilderness and Encampment River Wilderness.  Named for the famous battle between Indians and Fur Trappers in 1841, the 57-mile Battle Pass Scenic Byway runs through this area.  This byway is known for its scenic views, especially during fall when the colors are changing.</p><p> </p><div id=\"stcpDiv\"><article><div><p><span>Named for a famous Battle between Indians and Fur Trappers in 1841</span></p></div></article>- See more at: https://www.wyomingtourism.org/things-to-do/detail/Battle-Pass-Scenic-Byway/6990#sthash.TkLGolug.dpuf</div><p>This area has many activities such as hiking, fishing, mountain biking, camping, snowmobiling, and cross country skiing.  The Sierra Madre Range is managed by the Brush Creek/Hayden District.</p><p> </p><p>For more information contact or stop into the Ranger Station:</p><p>Brush Creek/Hayden Ranger Station<br/>2171 S. Highway 130<br/>Saratoga, WY 82331<br/>307-326-5258</p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "",
