          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Robbers Roost Campground is located next to Hwy 40 and the Fraser River near Winter Park.</p><p><strong>Facilities:</strong> There are 11 non-electric sites that will accommodate tents, trailers, and RVs. Each site contains a tent pad, fire grate and picnic table. Additional facilities included restrooms and trash service. Water is available at the Idlewild Campground 5.5 miles away.</p><p><strong>Natural Features:</strong> The campground is located in the forest so there is ample shade. The Fraser River runs by the campground.</p><p><strong>Recreation:</strong> Popular recreation activities include hiking in the Arapaho National Forest and the nearby <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/arp/recarea/?recid=80809\" rel=\"nofollow\">Vasquez Peak Wilderness</a>, scenic driving and wildlife viewing.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/stelprd3838642.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Campground Map</a> </p><p>View a COTREX map <a href=\"http://trails.colorado.gov/places/na~1983321\" rel=\"nofollow\">here</a>.</p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "Five miles south of Winter Park on US Highway 40 at the base of Berthoud Pass.",
