          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Cheesman Canyon Trailhead is located along Jefferson County Route 126, approximately 22 miles from south of Pine Junction from US Highway 285.</p><p>The five-mile <a href=\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/recarea/psicc/recreation/scenicdrivinginfo/recarea/?recid=12942&actid=50\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gill Trail #610 </a>follows the South Platte River through Cheesman Canyon and ends at the upper <a href=\"https://www.denverwater.org/recreation/cheesman-resevoir\" rel=\"nofollow\">Cheesman Reservoir</a> trailhead. The trail is difficult and steep in many sections and there are no facilities in the canyon. Help protect the canyon by staying on designated trails.</p><p><strong>User Regulations:</strong><br/><em>Trailhead</em></p><ul><li>No fees; donations accepted</li><li>No overnight use</li><li>No overnight parking</li><li>Park in designated spaces only</li></ul><p><em>Cheesman Canyon</em></p><ul><li>Flies and lures only</li><li>Catch and release only</li><li>Stay on designated trails</li><li>Dogs must be leashed at all times</li><li>Pack it in, Pack it out</li></ul><p><strong><em>Protect these waters from <a href=\"http://cpw.state.co.us/aboutus/Pages/ISP-ANS.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">Aquatic Nuisance Species</a>.</em></strong></p>",
