          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Hahns Peak/Bears Ears Ranger District includes about 500,000 acres of the Routt National Forest, and terrain ranges from sagebrush flats to forested mountains. There are a wide variety of year-round recreation opportunities available to visitors. The Ranger District office is in Steamboat Springs, Colo.</p><p> </p><p>Scroll down for area-specific activities, locations and maps...</p><p>Select <strong>California Park/Black Mountain</strong>, <strong>Mount Zirkel/Park Range</strong>, <b>North Routt,</b> or <b>Steamboat</b> under 'Areas & Activities' in the right-hand sidebar to find recreation sites on the Hahns Peak/Bears Ears Ranger District.</p>",
