          "FacilityDescription": "<p>The Cabin Bench Area Trail #104 begins at Forest Service Road #501 and ends at FSR #502. This trail travels along Cabin Bench above the East Fork Escalante Creek. A combination of this trail, FSR #502 and #501 creates about a 7.2 mile loop.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_DOCUMENTS/fseprd540489.pdf\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Ref Trail Map</a>   <a href=\"http://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/gmug/maps-pubs/?cid=stelprdb5441230\" rel=\"nofollow\">Geo-Reference Instructions</a></p>",
          "FacilityDirections": "<p><strong>From Delta:</strong> Turn west on Highway 348, 6th Street. Travel west and south on HWY 348 for approximately 4 miles to 25 Mesa Road. Continue on 25 Mesa Road for approximately 18 miles the National Forest Boundary where 25 Mesa Road becomes Forest Service Road #503. Continue on FSR #503 for approximately 4.2 miles to FSR #504. Follow FSR #504 for approximately 5.8 miles to FSR #501. Turn southwest on FSR #501, the trail access is approximately 1.1 miles on the north side of the road.</p><p><strong>From Montrose:</strong> Travel west on Highway 90 for approximately 23 miles to the intersection with Forest Service Road #402, Divide Road. Follow FSR #402 north for approximately 16.5 miles to FSR #503, Delta-Nulca Road. Turn north onto FSR #503 and continue for approximately 5.1 miles to FSR #504. Turn west onto FSR #504 and travel approximately 5.8 miles to FSR #501. Turn southwest on FSR #501, the trail access is approximately 1.1 miles on the north side of the road.</p>",
